<o:Table Id="o332">
<a:ObjectID>A19ABF60-8034-4671-B503-1B9DF90A98C7</a:ObjectID>
<a:Name>Segment Levels</a:Name>
<a:Code>TSEGMENTLVL</a:Code>
<a:CreationDate>1422954629</a:CreationDate>
<a:Creator>U001107</a:Creator>
<a:ModificationDate>1584624853</a:ModificationDate>
<a:Modifier>U008652</a:Modifier>
<a:Comment>This table defines the different Segment Levels available for a Segmentation as well as their labels.
All Segments defined for the Segmentation should match one of the registered Segment Levels (LVL_CT field of the TSEGMT table).
At least Level 0 level is mandatory to manage the Segments supporting Segmentation Criteria (via Rules).
Other levels may defined (up to level 5) may be defined for different &quot;segment aggregation&quot; levels (Segments containing sub-Segments).</a:Comment>
<a:TotalSavingCurrency/>
<a:Description>{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.21.2510;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 2013-05-29 / Omega 2-Phase 1B&#39;-OM-B-TRA01\par
