<o:Table Id="o334">
<a:ObjectID>EAFB4D85-17CE-4369-9864-EB11967CC218</a:ObjectID>
<a:Name>Segmentation Exception</a:Name>
<a:Code>TSEGMENTEXCEPT</a:Code>
<a:CreationDate>1422954629</a:CreationDate>
<a:Creator>U001107</a:Creator>
<a:ModificationDate>1584624853</a:ModificationDate>
<a:Modifier>U008652</a:Modifier>
<a:Comment>This table contains all exceptions for a given Segmentation.
It defines, for a given portfolio element (Contract, Section, Placement, depending on the Segmentation scope and granularity), the Segment to be assigned regardless of Segment Rules evaluations.
These exception are usually set by Segmentation administrators when encountering errors at segmentation evaluation (e.g. elements assigned to multiple Segments, very specific cases not included in the Rule criteria...).</a:Comment>
<a:TotalSavingCurrency/>
<a:Description>{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang1036{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}}
{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.21.2510;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 2013-05-29 / Omega 2-Phase 1B&#39;-OM-B-TRA01\par
- Creation\par
\par
2013-06-17 / Omega 2-Phase 1B&#39;-OM-B-TRA01\par
- last update fields become mandatory\par
- Removed Endorsement (not a supported granularity)\par
- corrected RTO_NF field name (ex. &quot;RTO_CF&quot;)\par
\par
2013-07-23 / Omega 2-Phase 1B&#39;-OM-B-TRA01\par
- Add SEGCTRTYP\par
\par
2013-09-17 / Omega 2-Phase 1B&#39;-OM-B-TRA01\par
- SGMT_CF changed to SGMT_NF\par
\par
2015-01-20 / Omega 2-Phase 2B&#39;-TRA01\par
- Merge SEG datamodel into EST datamodel\par
\par
}
</a:Description>
